 {m+n\choose j+k}\,,
\enddisplay
so the second sum is $1/{m+n\choose m}$ times the first.
And the first is just the special case $l=0$, $n=b$, $r=a$, $s=m+n-b$ of
\equ(5.|bc-quad|), so it is ${a+b\choose a}{m+n-a-b\choose n-a}$.

